SIMPLE: significative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Significative
<hw>Sig*nif"i*ca*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>significativus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>significatif</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Betokening or representing by an external
sign.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The holy symbols or signs are not barely
<qex>significative</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Brerewood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having signification or meaning; expressive of a
meaning or purpose; significant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither in the degrees of kindred they were destitute of
<qex>significative</qex> words.</q> <rj><qau>Camden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sig*nif"i*ca*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sig*nif"i*ca*tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Significator</ent>⟦br⟧
